#Calculating the #silhoutte  coefficient
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

#silhoutte co-efficent range is from -1 to 1 with 1 being best. It will tell how well clusters are separated

for n_cluster in range(2,14):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=n_cluster).fit(x)
    label = kmeans.labels_
    sil_coeff = silhouette_score(x, label, metric='euclidean')
    print("For n_clusters={}, The Silhouette Coefficient is {}".format(n_cluster, sil_coeff))

#separate the data set into two different arrays for the two different clusters
columns = ['Workclass', 'Education', 'Maritial-Status', 'Occupation', 'Relationship', 'Race', 'Sex', 'Native-Country', 'Income', 'Age', 'Education-Num', 'Capital-Gain', 'Capital-Loss', 'Hours-Per-Week']

workclass = df['Workclass']
education = df['Education']
maritialstatus = df['Maritial-Status']
occupation = df['Occupation']
relationship = df['Relationship']
race = df['Race']
sex = df['Sex']
nativecountry = df['Native-Country']
income = df['Income']
age = df['Age']
educationnum = df['Education-Num']
capitalgain = df['Capital-Gain']
capitalloss = df['Capital-Loss']
hoursperweek = df['Hours-Per-Week']
cluster = df['Cluster']

count0 = 0
count1 = 0

for i in df['Cluster']:
    if i == 0:
        count0+=1
    if i == 1:
        count1+=1

df0 = []*count0
df1 = []*count1

for i in range(len(df)):
    a = [workclass[i], education[i], maritialstatus[i], occupation[i], relationship[i], race[i], sex[i], nativecountry[i], income[i], age[i], educationnum[i], capitalgain[i], capitalloss[i], hoursperweek[i]]
    if df['Cluster'][i] == 0:
        df0.append(a)
    if df['Cluster'][i] == 1:
        df1.append(a)

        
df0array = np.array(df0)
df1array = np.array(df1)

#separate the data set into two different arrays for the two different clusters
columns = ['Workclass', 'Education', 'Maritial-Status', 'Occupation', 'Relationship', 'Race', 'Sex', 'Native-Country', 'Income', 'Age', 'Education-Num', 'Capital-Gain', 'Capital-Loss', 'Hours-Per-Week']

workclass = df['Workclass']
education = df['Education']
maritialstatus = df['Maritial-Status']
occupation = df['Occupation']
relationship = df['Relationship']
race = df['Race']
sex = df['Sex']
nativecountry = df['Native-Country']
income = df['Income']
age = df['Age']
educationnum = df['Education-Num']
capitalgain = df['Capital-Gain']
capitalloss = df['Capital-Loss']
hoursperweek = df['Hours-Per-Week']
cluster = df['Clusters']


count0 = 0
count1 = 0

for i in df['Clusters']:
    if i == 0:
        count0+=1
    if i == 1:
        count1+=1

df0 = []*count0
df1 = []*count1

for i in range(len(df)):
    a = [workclass[i], education[i], maritialstatus[i], occupation[i], relationship[i], race[i], sex[i], nativecountry[i], income[i], age[i], educationnum[i], capitalgain[i], capitalloss[i], hoursperweek[i]]
    if df['Clusters'][i] == 0:
        df0.append(a)
    if df['Clusters'][i] == 1:
        df1.append(a)

        
df0array = np.array(df0)
df1array = np.array(df1)
